MBOMBELA Dynamic Vision Optometrists have come to the aid of a family by sponsoring four-year-old Cyrus Potgieter with frames and lenses for absolutely no charge. Optometrist Mr Keith Kirton came to their aid after reading about Cyrus s dilemma in the Lowvelder. This after the paper reported about the family who have two special-needs children are still short of funds to pay for an eye operation which has to be performed next week.Cyrus Potgieter (4) was born with ptosis, commonly known as lazy-eye . He had his first operation after he was born, and now has to have another procedure to lift his eyelid. He will be needing an operation every two years as he grows.Hi-Tech Security Nelspruit staff have raised now R15 000 towards their plight, but the eye operation itself will cost R18 000. Cyrus parents Mr Huey and Ms Petru Potgieter, explained that the operation has to be performed in Pretoria. His new glasses would have cost another R4 000. Thanks to Dynamic Vision Optometrists, this will be one less burden on the family. We are so thankful to Hi-Tech Security and to Dynamic Vision Optometrists for trying to help us, a thousand blessings to all their staff, Petru said.Additional aid for Cyrus has come in the form of Gerhard Lourens Attorneys, which helped the family set up a trust account which will be managed by the firm, free of charge. The couple s other son, Xerxes (2), has Down s syndrome. Pro Gracia for disabled children, has offered him a place when he is old enough to go to school. They said they will help arrange a payment plan for the fees, Pertu said.Any donations towards Cyrus operation can now be deposited directly into:Name: Gerhard Lourens Trust Account, bank:Absa, account number: 406 798 6974, ACB: 632 005, reference: Little Cyrus.Read more here: Four-year-old still needs funds for an eye operation